    <name>Pro Tips: Expert Learning</name>
    <intro>&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</intro>
    <introformat>1</introformat>
    <content>&lt;p dir="ltr" style="text-align: left;"&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;span style="font-size: 1.7rem;"&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Pro%20Tip.png" alt="Hand holding a plant" width="140" height="136" role="presentation" class="atto_image_button_text-top"&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;ol role="list" start="1"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Use case studies in your instruction:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;To introduce or conclude an instructional topic, adults may&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;be engaged by a relevant situation&amp;nbsp;(case) because they can&amp;nbsp;then analyze that case to identify and&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;practice applying potential&amp;nbsp;solutions (study).&amp;nbsp;We are using captioned video, along with access to&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;a transcript, to support variability in all learners, whatever their context.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;​&lt;/span&gt;Because they are real-life examples, case&amp;nbsp;studies that include multiple options for perception&amp;nbsp;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;further optimize&amp;nbsp;relevance, value, and authenticity in learning. (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Engagement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Principle,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement/recruiting-interest/relevance-value-authenticity" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Checkpoint 7.2&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;)&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Frame all participants (administrators, teachers, volunteers and students) as learners:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Adult&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;learning theory reminds us that adults benefit when they can participate in the design of the&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;learning environment, experiences, and activities. UDL can help to frame not only ‘students’ but&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;instructional members - teachers, administrators, volunteers, etc. – as models of expert learning,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;who continuously develop their purpose and motivation, resourcefulness and knowledge, and&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;strategic, goal-oriented habits.&amp;nbsp; (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Engagement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Principle,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement/effort-persistence/goals-objectives" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Checkpoint 8.1&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;p xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US" paraid="0" paraeid="{2668ea3d-b027-4624-914f-67c53cf67e0f}{37}" data-ccp-props="{&amp;quot;335551550&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335551620&amp;quot;:1,&amp;quot;335559683&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335559685&amp;quot;:550,&amp;quot;335559731&amp;quot;:-540,&amp;quot;335559737&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562764&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;335562765&amp;quot;:1.14,&amp;quot;335562766&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562767&amp;quot;:0,&amp;quot;335562768&amp;quot;:4,&amp;quot;335562769&amp;quot;:6}" data-indent="-540"&gt;​&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Leverage group learning through collaboration and community:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Using group tasks,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;educators&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;can facilitate diverse groups of adult learners to work effectively together by setting clear goals&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;for the collaborative work and articulating roles for the activities. This can be especially&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;important with autism and learning difficulties. Help participants build trust and effectively work&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;together by creating clear goals for collaboration, defining each role, and even providing&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;questions or prompts for groups to discuss. Another approach for long-term projects could be a&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Communities of Practice model, where adults might self-organize based on shared or different&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;goals and expertise. (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Engagement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Principle,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement/effort-persistence/collaboration-community" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Checkpoint 8.3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span&gt;For more ideas on fostering collaboration and community, review&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://lvp.digitalpromiseglobal.org/content-area/adult-learner/strategies/communities-of-practice-adult-learner/summary" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Communities of Practice&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;resources from Digital Promise&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;. At the systems level,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;administrators&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&amp;nbsp;can support adult&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;learning and belonging by instituting cohorts, or larger-scale groups of learners that progress&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;through a program together. Although various cohort models exist, they tend to involve&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;community-building activities or events, as well as organized course sequencing or pathways,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;so that learners gradually come to know the members of their cohort through repeated&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;contact. For more on adult learning and belonging, review the summary or the full report:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://worlded.org/cultivating-a-sense-of-belonging-and-community-in-adult-education/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Cultivating a Sense of Belonging and Community in Adult Education&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Develop community using icebreakers:&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;“These were fun, low-pressure activities designed to let&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;students and teachers get to know each other and start to form trusting relationships,” Nashua&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Adult Learning (NH).&amp;nbsp;Icebreakers can support the development of community, by helping staff&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;and learners understand and appreciate each other in a variety of ways. Icebreakers can be silly&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;(What is your favorite karaoke song?) or they can be meaningful and help participants articulate&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;barriers or appreciate persistence. For example, one icebreaker question could be: What did you&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;have to overcome to make to class today? (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Engagement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Principle,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement/recruiting-interest/threats-distractions" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Checkpoint 7.3&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Collaborate with educators (teachers and volunteers) to identify targeted professional&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;development opportunities:&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Foster an expert learning community by actively seeking feedback&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;and/or conducting scheduled informal observations to identify the types of professional&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;development educators want/need, as well as the best ways to deliver it (&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;Engagement&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;&amp;nbsp;Principle,&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://udlguidelines.cast.org/engagement/effort-persistence/collaboration-community" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer"&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;UDL Checkpoint 8.3&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;span data-usefontface="false" data-contrast="none" xml:lang="EN-US" lang="EN-US"&gt;).&lt;/span&gt;​&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;&lt;img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/divider%20wave.png" alt="Divider Wave" width="1920" height="195" role="presentation" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_text-bottom"&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content>
